WEBVTT

00:06.818 --> 00:10.923
So have you ever missed a moment?

00:12.405 --> 00:19.694
You know, you're having your friends over the games on and you go to the refrigerator to get something to drink and turn around and everyone starts screaming.

00:20.355 --> 00:24.279
And you realize you just missed the most important play of the entire game.

00:24.299 --> 00:29.746
You missed the moment, or you're invited to your daughters.

00:30.562 --> 00:47.941
and she's been practicing these lines, and in the middle of that play, you get a text, and it's something at work, and it's something so important, you're thinking, it's just gonna take a second, and as you respond to that, you hear people clapping, and you realize you just missed what your daughter's been rehearsing for months, you just missed a moment.

00:49.262 --> 00:51.945
Anybody ever forget the birthday of a friend or family member?

00:53.547 --> 00:54.949
Anybody ever forget an anniversary?

00:57.712 --> 00:59.794
There's no going back from some of these moments, right?

01:00.194 --> 01:07.146
See, the thing with moments is that they happen so often, they seem so ordinary, that you only realize the weight of a moment after it's over.

01:07.166 --> 01:11.454
After you look back and go, man, I can't believe that wasn't an ordinary moment and I missed it.

01:12.856 --> 01:13.537
And here's the thing.

01:14.299 --> 01:23.034
The first Christmas for most people, which is an ordinary night, most people, the first Christmas, missed the whole thing.

01:24.897 --> 01:25.458
They missed it.

01:25.538 --> 01:32.148
Angels, they missed the star, they missed the celebration, they missed the birth of Jesus, they missed it because it was just an ordinary night.

01:33.730 --> 01:41.582
But a few that ordinary became extraordinary because they looked, they saw, they witnessed.

01:41.602 --> 01:42.323
And here's what I believe.

01:42.363 --> 01:46.189
Most people, this Christmas season, this Advent season will miss the moments.

01:47.210 --> 01:48.632
It'll just be an ordinary couple of weeks.

01:48.672 --> 01:51.977
It's busy with parties and things and all the gifts you have to buy and all the stress of all the things.

01:52.017 --> 01:55.122
And it's easy to go through an entire Christmas season to miss

01:55.298 --> 01:55.999
those moments.

01:56.019 --> 02:06.510
And so the next couple of weeks, we're going to be focusing on this idea of how can ordinary moments be transformed to extraordinary moments by the way that we view them.

02:06.550 --> 02:17.681
And so I'm just going to give you a simple definition of ordinary, ordinary, possessing no special or distinctive features, something common, average, or mundane.

02:19.843 --> 02:22.546
And then how do we as the people of God say, no, no, no, no.

02:23.298 --> 02:25.180
Those moments aren't just common or average.

02:26.101 --> 02:32.787
If we have the eyes of the heart to see what God is speaking, what God is doing, then we don't have to miss the moments.

02:32.907 --> 02:40.114
And so I want to share with you just a few of those opportunities for people to turn and see something that looks very ordinary.

02:40.134 --> 02:41.816
And the first one is the story of Moses.

02:43.417 --> 02:47.681
In Exodus chapter three, Moses is wandering around in the wilderness.

02:49.163 --> 02:52.466
You see, 40 years earlier, he was the prince of Egypt.

02:53.666 --> 02:55.408
40 years earlier, he was in the palace.

02:55.428 --> 02:56.270
He was the man.

02:56.350 --> 02:59.414
He was well educated and well fed and well honored.

02:59.774 --> 03:07.645
People wanted to hear what he had to say, but well, in a moment of impulse, he tries to become the leader of his people Israel.

03:07.705 --> 03:09.628
He kills an Egyptian and now he's a fugitive.

03:10.669 --> 03:16.677
And so this man with so much promise, so much education, so much honor becomes a nobody.

03:18.039 --> 03:20.082
And he's wandering around feeding sheep.

03:21.442 --> 03:33.635
The only thing he hears for 40 years is, and his fine palace clothes or now shepherd's clothes and tattered sandals walking around in the dust, forgotten.

03:34.977 --> 03:38.841
Life has passed Moses by.

03:40.422 --> 03:46.589
And you're probably not going to find a figure in the Bible who was this high in his early life and this low later on in his life.

03:47.590 --> 03:51.154
And here's what happens as Moses is wandering around

03:51.618 --> 03:53.020
in the wilderness.

03:53.801 --> 04:01.171
Exodus chapter three, verse two, there, the angel of the Lord appeared to him in flames of fire from within a bush.

04:01.191 --> 04:03.795
And Moses saw that though the bush was on fire, he did not burn up.

04:04.476 --> 04:08.801
So Moses thought, I will go over and see this strange sight why the bush does not burn up.

04:10.103 --> 04:11.024
Look closely at verse four.

04:11.285 --> 04:19.035
Now, when the Lord saw that he had gone over to look, God called to him from within the bush, Moses, Moses.

04:20.157 --> 04:20.978
And Moses said,

04:21.218 --> 04:21.679
Here I am.

04:22.960 --> 04:28.949
Do not come any closer, God said, take off your sandals for the place where your standing is holy ground.

04:30.731 --> 04:38.062
What's happened, Moses wandering around, probably living in a sense of regret that he missed his moment, that he has no purpose, but God's eye is still on Moses.

04:38.542 --> 04:40.725
Because if you're not dead, that you are not done.

04:40.745 --> 04:42.969
You know that God's eye is always on his people.

04:44.270 --> 04:46.834
And so this bush that starts burning.

04:47.682 --> 04:53.948
A bush that maybe Moses had walked by 100 times in his life and 40 years in the wilderness, you walk by a lot of bushes.

04:55.189 --> 05:02.936
And God waited for Moses to look and turn and see before he spoke.

05:02.996 --> 05:04.478
That's what verse four says.

05:05.459 --> 05:08.001
So my question is like, how many times did he not see?

05:08.301 --> 05:10.784
Did he not notice that God wanted to speak to him?

05:10.804 --> 05:15.308
I have no idea, but when Moses finally said, what's going on here?

05:16.369 --> 05:17.650
God calls his name.

05:18.274 --> 05:25.145
and says, I want you to take off your sandals because the place you're standing is holy ground.

05:25.165 --> 05:28.971
Now for 40 years, that ground he walked on was ordinary.

05:30.613 --> 05:31.154
It was common.

05:32.877 --> 05:33.618
It was mundane.

05:33.678 --> 05:34.279
It was average.

05:34.299 --> 05:43.393
Nothing special about it until God spoke when Moses turned, which makes me think, are there moments in my life?

05:43.473 --> 05:46.578
Are there moments in your life that feel very ordinary

05:47.458 --> 05:50.423
But if we stopped in turn and say, God, what are you speaking?

05:50.443 --> 05:56.213
What are you saying that it would turn into this extraordinary holy moment?

05:56.253 --> 05:58.557
And we'd hear the calling of God, we'd hear his voice.

05:58.577 --> 06:01.983
Listen, Moses is the only person who experienced this moment.

06:02.003 --> 06:04.507
400 years before this, a man named Jacob.

06:05.448 --> 06:09.275
Jacob who became Israel, who was the father of the nation of Israel.

06:10.297 --> 06:13.522
Well, he had a rough moment in his life.

06:13.666 --> 06:19.672
lied to his father, he stole his brother's birthright, and now his brother wants to kill him, and now he's a fugitive himself, like Moses.

06:19.712 --> 06:21.113
He runs into the wilderness.

06:22.434 --> 06:23.916
And there's got to be a sense of anxiety.

06:23.936 --> 06:24.897
He's a mama's boy.

06:25.397 --> 06:26.779
He's used to being taken care of.

06:26.799 --> 06:29.321
He's used to the good life, and now he's all on his own.

06:29.361 --> 06:30.863
He has no way to provide for himself.

06:32.244 --> 06:33.845
His future is very uncertain.

06:33.885 --> 06:36.888
He's probably thinking to himself, why did I say that?

06:36.928 --> 06:37.769
Why did I do that?

06:37.809 --> 06:40.412
And fill with a deep sense of regret, but you can't go back.

06:41.733 --> 06:42.834
He can only go forward.

06:43.810 --> 06:49.017
And so all he has that night in the wilderness is a stone that he uses as a pillow.

06:50.299 --> 06:55.586
And he goes to sleep with all the anxiety, with all the shame, with all the regret, with all the stuff.

06:55.626 --> 06:58.029
It just looks like an average night in the middle of nowhere.

06:58.951 --> 07:07.062
But when he falls asleep, he dreams of this stairway, this ladder from heaven and angels descending and descending and God speaks to him in this place.

07:07.242 --> 07:13.170
And when he wakes up, he says, surely God was in this place.

07:14.498 --> 07:15.379
and I didn't know it.

07:16.821 --> 07:19.003
And I love that line.

07:19.023 --> 07:20.826
God was in this place.

07:20.866 --> 07:26.913
It seemed ordinary when I went to sleep, but when I dreamed and when I opened my eyes, I see God was speaking to me in this place.

07:26.933 --> 07:38.387
He said, how awesome in this place, I'm gonna name this place Bethel, the house of God, an ordinary place in the middle of the wilderness, becomes a place where God reveals himself to Jacob and changes who he is.

07:38.447 --> 07:42.252
And this, again, is another moment, this idea.

07:43.393 --> 07:44.274
Surely God,

07:44.418 --> 07:49.886
is in this place, and I didn't know it.

07:49.906 --> 07:51.308
Now, I want you to think of your yesterday.

07:51.348 --> 07:55.694
Was God in all those places and spaces where you were?

07:55.734 --> 07:58.218
And did you know it?

07:58.258 --> 07:59.479
Were you aware of it today?

07:59.540 --> 08:09.774
Will God be in the spaces and places as you drive home, as you go out to brunch, as you have this meal, as you talk to a friend, as you play a game?

08:09.974 --> 08:12.498
Is God in all those moments?

08:12.962 --> 08:17.027
The Bible reminds us God is everywhere present.

08:18.168 --> 08:23.434
Psalm 139, there is nowhere you can go where God is not.

08:23.454 --> 08:24.095
Isn't that good news?

08:24.716 --> 08:33.606
Psalm 139, you can't go to the darkest, deepest pit or the highest mountain and not experience the presence of God.

08:33.626 --> 08:35.609
We call this omni-presence.

08:35.649 --> 08:36.850
God is everywhere.

08:37.314 --> 08:42.822
It's not the same as pantheism where God is Mother Earth and she is the rocks and the trees.

08:42.882 --> 08:49.271
No, no, here's our Abraham Kuiper describes the sovereignty of God over all creation.

08:50.272 --> 09:00.206
There is not a square inch and the whole domain of our human existence over which Christ who is sovereign overall does not cry mine.

09:03.030 --> 09:05.874
Jesus made all things.

09:06.050 --> 09:13.160
Everything is by him and through him and for him and everything in all creation worships its creator.

09:13.220 --> 09:17.005
This is who God is, the sovereign God over all and God.

09:17.786 --> 09:18.928
It doesn't miss any moments.

09:20.109 --> 09:35.250
And so I pray for us as we talk through this series that we would have the eyes to see a heightened awareness that all the ordinary moments all around us, that God is present and God is speaking and wants to have a relationship with us and well,

09:36.162 --> 09:38.505
We're gonna practice that in a few ways.

09:39.467 --> 09:41.530
So what would it mean just to think about a couple of common things?

09:41.550 --> 09:43.312
I wanna get our minds started.

09:43.352 --> 09:52.666
So like, every morning I wake up, one of the first things I do is I make myself a cup of coffee.

09:54.088 --> 09:54.428
Anybody?

09:54.448 --> 09:56.511
Okay, a few of you.

09:57.453 --> 10:04.082
Now, you can just drink the cup of coffee and go in your day, or you can pause, and you can smell the coffee.

10:05.794 --> 10:08.718
And you can say, God, thank you for coffee.

10:11.462 --> 10:14.046
The Bible says, taste and see that God is good.

10:14.066 --> 10:24.320
You know, God made our sense of smell and our sense of taste in every good food or drink that you've ever smelled or eaten or drank yourself is a gift of a generous God to you.

10:24.461 --> 10:32.071
And so just a moment with a cup of coffee and a quiet moment, God, thank you for this coffee.

10:33.133 --> 10:33.874
You're pausing.

10:34.690 --> 10:36.032
doesn't have to be ordinary.

10:37.614 --> 10:50.390
You walk out to your car and you're walking by a sidewalk and you see this, a flower emerging in the crack of a sidewalk.

10:50.410 --> 10:53.695
Now, in your cynical self, I'm like, I need to get some weed killer and kill that thing.

10:56.118 --> 10:59.282
Or you can say, God, how extraordinary

11:00.354 --> 11:10.848
that in the crack of a sidewalk, you allow life to merge, and not just life, but a beautiful picture of your creativity and beauty and generosity.

11:10.868 --> 11:20.140
And then you might think, hey, those cracks in my life, those things that look great in my life, how would something beautiful emerge in those places?

11:20.500 --> 11:21.842
What about a dinner?

11:22.050 --> 11:22.991
around a table.

11:23.011 --> 11:25.214
You're going to be doing this a lot over the Christmas season.

11:25.594 --> 11:31.081
So instead of saying to the kids, hey, eat your vegetables and clean up and stop making a mess and say something nice to your brother.

11:32.723 --> 11:37.068
Instead of arguing with your roommate over, politics are all the anger and stuff of the day.

11:37.088 --> 11:40.112
Why don't I just stop in the moment and just go, God, thank you for a good friend.

11:41.614 --> 11:42.755
God, thank you for a family.

11:44.017 --> 11:45.759
God, thank you to the good and the bad.

11:45.879 --> 11:48.562
You've been with us in every

11:48.866 --> 11:52.471
moment in a simple meal can become a moment of gratitude and joy.

11:52.751 --> 11:54.113
It can become an active worship.

11:55.155 --> 12:00.021
Just a couple of weeks ago, we celebrated 40 years of Calvary, a generation, and we were praying for good weather.

12:00.101 --> 12:05.469
And well, in between the services, the weather wasn't great, but then all of a sudden, we saw this over our church.

12:06.951 --> 12:11.056
And we're like, God, even in bad weather, you are good.

12:11.076 --> 12:12.458
Your promise is on us.

12:12.478 --> 12:13.339
You're speaking to us.

12:13.359 --> 12:14.000
You love us.

12:14.461 --> 12:15.763
And it became for us.

12:16.864 --> 12:18.226
For those of us who noticed,

12:18.754 --> 12:24.101
an act of worship, ordinary things becoming extraordinary.

12:24.922 --> 12:27.725
And so today we're going to talk about just one of those things.

12:28.867 --> 12:40.521
The simple, the simple thing of light, light seems so simple, so easy to look past.

12:40.561 --> 12:47.570
And when John writes his gospel the first Christmas, he doesn't talk about like Matthew, the dreams that Joseph God or

12:47.938 --> 12:49.160
the star in the sky.

12:49.740 --> 12:54.026
He doesn't talk like Luke does about the song that Mary wrote or the shepherds in the sky.

12:54.327 --> 13:02.017
John describes the Christmas story in light seven times in just the first few verses of John's opening of the Christmas story.

